http://mindscape.io

Each user builds a hierarchy of nodes
  (each node is a post),
linked together in a radially expanding graph
  (each link is an arrow between nodes).
Nodes 

Each link can go between a sequence of nodes, e.g. in a presentation or a train of thought
In our interface they are displayed in the order of searching or recognizing or rendering or enumerating; 
  we often display information in a tree shape that
    is intuitively visualizable, with material behavior,
    allows for sorting (e.g. in a binary search tree
    
  
    taxonomic trees in biology,
    linguistic tree of root words to prefixes/suffixes 
    linguistic tree of Chinese radical/root to phonetic symbols,
    genes? with crossing over? 
    nested folder (directory-subdirectory) tree shaped file system on popular personal computers,

    and hierarchical outline structures,
    

overlay your dish with other people's dishes and wire cycles between identical nodes
to form one big dish/mandala.
The service provides coordinating nodes, representing 4D of space-time to seed the integration of personal hierarchies.
A model of the Internet.

